I":<p><img src="http://localhost:4000/images/Goddard.jpg" class="img-responsive" width="25%" style="float: right" /></p>

<p>I am currently a lecturer in the <a href="http://www.maths.ed.ac.uk/">School of Mathematics</a> at the <a href="http://www.ed.ac.uk/">University of Edinburgh</a>.</p>

<p>Previous to this, I have been a postdoc in the groups of <a href="http://www.imperial.ac.uk/AP/faces/pages/read/Home.jsp?person=s.kalliadasis&amp;_adf.ctrl-state=noxc94gbi_3&amp;_afrRedirect=292205271445195&quot;&gt;Serafim Kalliadasis">Serafim Kalliadasis</a> (<a href="http://www3.imperial.ac.uk/">Imperial College</a>, <a href="http://www3.imperial.ac.uk/complexmultiphasesystems">Chemical Engineering</a>) and <a href="http://www.mathematik.tu-darmstadt.de/~betz/">Volker Betz</a> (<a href="http://www2.warwick.ac.uk/">University of Warwick</a>, <a href="http://www2.warwick.ac.uk/fac/sci/maths/">Mathematics</a>, now <a href="http://www.tu-darmstadt.de/index.en.jsp">TU Darmstadt</a>, <a href="http://www3.mathematik.tu-darmstadt.de/en/fb/mathe/startseite.html">Mathematics</a>).  I undertook my PhD under <a href="http://www-m7.ma.tum.de/bin/view/Analysis/GeroFriesecke">Gero Friesecke</a> (University of Warwick, Maths, now <a href="http://www.tum.de/en/homepage/">TU Munich</a>, 
<a href="http://www-m7.ma.tum.de/bin/view/Analysis/WebHome">Mathematics</a>).</p>

<p>Broadly speaking, my research concerns modelling, analysis and numerics for complex, multiscale systems.  My work has applications in chemistry, physics, engineering and biology.  Both the areas and techniques used in my research are very broad-ranging. I’m always happy to discuss my work with anyone, especially mathematicians, applied scientists and prospective PhD students.</p>

<p>Trivia:
I have <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Erdos_number">Erdös</a> number 4: Me –&gt; Volker Betz –&gt; Peter Mörters –&gt; David Preiss –&gt; Paul Erdös, and <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bacon_number">Bacon number</a> 3: Me –(G103)–&gt; Patrick Niknejad –(Harry Potter)–&gt; Gary Oldman –(Criminal Law)–&gt; Kevin Bacon.</p>

<p>This gives me an <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Erd%C5%91s%E2%80%93Bacon_number">Erdös-Bacon</a> number of 7.</p>

